Solomon by the example of the Piſmire, would bring idle ſlothfull people to honeſt labour. The Pſalmiſt warns all to truſt in God and his providence; yet not ſo that we ſhould omit any thing of our duty, for ſo God doth govern all things, that he will have us to uſe lawfull means, and effect all our works by them. So when Chriſt faith, Be not carefull for the morrow;
Luke 12.15. Theoph.
 he doth not forbid us to work, or to give our ſelves over to care, and to neglect Gods providence, for we are commanded to till the ground and to take care to live.

